# CLI changes and validation

When you **change or validate CLI functionality** (especially when the CLI is consumed by another repo), **always use the cli-rc-testing subagent**. Do not complete the task by suggesting the user "publish an RC and try it"—invoke the agent so it publishes the RC and verifies in the consumer (bump → build → publish → update consumer → `mise install` + consumer command → confirm output) before you mark the work done.

**Publish auth:** NPM_TOKEN is in AWS Secrets Manager secret `devops`. Write `.npmrc.publish` with `//registry.npmjs.org/:_authToken=<token>`, run `npm publish ... --userconfig .npmrc.publish`. Add `.npmrc.publish` to `.gitignore` and leave it locally; no need to delete after publish. See `skills/cli-rc-testing/SKILL.md` for the one-liner.
